{"TopicId":129575,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"OOPS: Kerbal Alarm Clock lets you cheat on Rescue Contracts","CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-09T14:08:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-09T14:08:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just accidentally did this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-indent:-.25in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E1.\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:7pt \u0027Times New Roman\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003EHave a rescue contact (a Kerbal in a ship you don\u2019t own yet)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-indent:-.25in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E2.\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:7pt \u0027Times New Roman\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003EView the ship in Tracking Station\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-indent:-.25in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E3.\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:7pt \u0027Times New Roman\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003ESet an alarm for that ship (at any time)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-indent:-.25in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E4.\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:7pt \u0027Times New Roman\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003EClick on the alarm in KAC\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-indent:-.25in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E5.\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:7pt \u0027Times New Roman\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003EClick \u201Cjump to ship\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-indent:-.25in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E6.\u003Cspan style=\u0022font:7pt \u0027Times New Roman\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003ESuddenly your Rescue Contract is completed. (He\u2019s not home yet, but you do have command of the Kerbal)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had a rescue contract and the guy flung past the Moon out into interplanetary space.\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0 \u003C/span\u003EI was trying to set an alarm for when he\u2019d swing past Kerbin again, and I accidentally completed the contract.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u00A0\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThought you guys should know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(KAC should fix this bug)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRoger and Out,\u003Cbr\u003E\nBrainlord Mesomorph\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deutherius","CreatedById":125381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-09T14:17:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis also works for asteroids. I have accidentally switched to a few while marking their intercept dates with Kerbin. Admittedly not as useful as the rescue bug, but it does give you an early look at the rocks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"suicidejunkie","CreatedById":155878,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-09T14:50:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCompleted?\u00A0 You mean just the first step, not the whole thing right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have a lifesupport mod, that kind of bug would just kill the victim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-09T15:57:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222354452\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022129575\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452351000\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155878\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022suicidejunkie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, suicidejunkie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCompleted?\u00A0 You mean just the first step, not the whole thing right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-09T16:06:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be more effective if you had posted this in the KAC thread.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"charfa","CreatedById":113539,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-09T16:12:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257838\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0022\u003E@TriggerAu\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0shold be interested.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-09T16:31:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222354507\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022129575\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452355560\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be more effective if you had posted this in the KAC thread.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis there one?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAttn Mod: pls move this thread. TY\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-10T14:41:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not a bug. In the KAC thread (Yes there is one) there was discussion of this when it was implemented. There were warnings about it (I think with Asteroids only as perhaps Rescue Contracts were not a thing at the time but I may be misremembering) and there is a setting somewhere in the options that will turn it off if you prefer. I actually thought it was off by default. I would also not be surprised if it was mentioned in the first post of that thread, the readme, or both.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}